## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID. |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Errors if zero or more than one tool matches. |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | AI tool integer ID. Use this in an agent's `tool_ids`. |
| `name` | Tool name (the stable identifier, e.g. `search`). |
| `description` | Human-readable description of what the tool does. |
| `handler` | Backend handler identifier the tool dispatches to (e.g. `mcp.list_resources`). Informational. |
| `input_schema` | The tool's **JSON Schema** (as a JSON string) describing its input parameters. |
| `required_permission` | The permission a caller must hold to invoke the tool, or empty if none (e.g. `app.resources.read`, `app.session.read`, `app.resources.session`). |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp (when the tool was seeded). |

## Builtin tool names

Tool names are stable identifiers seeded from the backend registry. A
representative set:

| tool name | purpose |
|---|---|
| `search` | Search inventory (resources, locations, etc.). |
| `inspect` | Inspect a single object in detail. |
| `diagnose` | Run diagnostics against a target. |
| `list_changelog` | List changelog / history entries. |
| `list_sessions` | List active or recent sessions. |
| `list_events` | List events. |
| `list_skills` | List discoverable AI skills. |
| `load_skill` | Load a skill's body on demand. |
| `get_command_output` | Fetch the output of a command. |
| `get_session_commands` | List commands run in a session. |
| `get_session_command_output` | Fetch the output of a session command. |
| `inject_session_command` | Inject a command into a live session. |

This list is **instance- and version-dependent** â€” it is generated from backend
code, so it is **not** guaranteed exhaustive. Query your instance with this data
source (by name) for the authoritative set and the current `id`, `input_schema`,
and `required_permission` of each tool.
